<br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://files.sobservers.com/New%20Files/nut/AO/evade.jpg"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
<br>
The step in requirements from elusive target to fleet foot is huge, but the increased effectiveness is small.  When we get elusive target at level ~45 the 50 point boost to evades is very useful.  By the time we can use fleet foot we are level ~95 and the extra 35 points of evades is fairly insignificant compared to the attack skills our evades are matched up against. The additional 14 NCU required is a pretty stiff cost for that extra 35 points of evades.  It’s a bit of a letdown to finally learn the fleet foot nano and see no difference other than NCU space.<br>
In addition, these buffs do not stack with fixer run buffs and can be trumped by fixer nanos that offer much lower evades.<br>
<br>
Possible “fixes” for this nano line: <br>
-Add nano resist buff in addition to the other evades. <br>
-Increase buff substantially for “fleet foot” or reduce its nanoskill requirements and add another nano in between Fleet foot and Reduce inertia<br>
-reduce NCU requirement for fleet foot to make it a desirable (although not very effective) upgrade to elusive target.<br>
<br>
A long discussion about the overall effectiveness could be inserted here.  But that issue has been debated without clear answers for a while.  In order to understand evades we need to understand how the AGG/DEF bar works.  <br>
